    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Hi @Haroenv ,\r\n\r\nOur datas structure :\r\nhit : { best_offer : { merchant : {  name: \"AAA\" }  },   other_offers :  [  {  merchant : {  name: \"BBB\" }  },  ]}\r\n\r\nI would like to use a refinementList to count all the hits per merchants (on best and others)\r\nFor example : \r\n- AAA (1)\r\n- BBB (1) <--- this one doesn't show up if we use only \"best_offer\" \r\n\r\nI could use only one attribute \"best_offer.merchant.name\"  on refinementList.\r\nI need both \"best_offer.merchant.name\" and \"other_offers.merchant.name\" and my structure can't be modified...\r\nSo i would like to create a custom widget but informations are a bit incomplet.\r\n\r\nThanks",
