  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "This is a very advanced use case, but the way to go is: \r\n\r\n1. make a custom connector\r\n\r\nYou will have to base it on https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/blob/develop/src/connectors/refinement-list/connectRefinementList.js\r\n\r\nthe main difference however should be that it doesn't need to work with 1 attribute, but with multiple. \r\n\r\nYou will also need to do the sorting or merging of the lists yourself.\r\n\r\n2. ignore the jQuery parts of the tutorial and use vanilla JS for the rendering\r\n\r\nBasically on every \"render\" (every time the render function gets called in your connector) need to construct DOM for a refinement list to work as expected. \r\n\r\nDoes that help you?  ",
